            "title": "A creche \u201cIGN\u00c1CIO DE LOYOLA TORRES\u201d (1966-1997) e o ber\u00e7\u00e1rio municipal \u201cM\u00c3E CRISTINA\u201d (1997-2013) : na hist\u00f3ria da educa\u00e7\u00e3o infantil em Marilia/SP",
            "abstract": [
                "Por que conhecer a hist\u00f3ria da educa\u00e7\u00e3o infantil na cidade de Mar\u00edlia/SP, em especial, da Creche \u201cIgn\u00e1cio de Loyola Torres\u201d e do Ber\u00e7\u00e1rio Municipal \u201cM\u00e3e Cristina\u201d? Essas s\u00e3o quest\u00f5es que nortearam a pesquisa de mestrado de Josiane de Moura Dias Marquizeli, cujos resultados s\u00e3o publicados neste livro. Tomando como objeto de estudo a institui\u00e7\u00e3o de educa\u00e7\u00e3o infantil emque atuou, a autora desenvolveu rigorosa pesquisa documental e bibliogr\u00e1fica, contribuindo para a compreens\u00e3o de aspectos at\u00e9 ent\u00e3o pouco ou nada explorados da hist\u00f3ria da educa\u00e7\u00e3o infantil em Mar\u00edlia. Por meio do conhecimento do passado, a pesquisa possibilitou a compreens\u00e3o do presente e dos debates e a\u00e7\u00f5es travados desde pelo menos a d\u00e9cada de 1990 para o reconhecimento do direito das crian\u00e7as pequenas a mais do que serem cuidadas. Muitos foram os avan\u00e7os, mas ainda muitas s\u00e3o as necessidades e urg\u00eancias para que se efetive plenamente esse direito. A sociedade civil tem importante fun\u00e7\u00e3o nesse processo. E tamb\u00e9m para isso contribuem os resultados da pesquisa de Josiane. Este \u00e9, portanto, livro indispens\u00e1vel para professores, cuidadores, gestores escolares e da educa\u00e7\u00e3o p\u00fablica, pesquisadores, estudantes de gradua\u00e7\u00e3o e p\u00f3s-gradua\u00e7\u00e3o, pais e m\u00e3es. E pode tamb\u00e9m ele ser considerado como mais um instrumento de luta e um convite para o necess\u00e1rio debate e urgentes a\u00e7\u00f5es coletivas em defesa da educa\u00e7\u00e3o de nossas crian\u00e7as para a constru\u00e7\u00e3o de uma sociedade mais justa e inclusiva",
                "Why learn about the history of early childhood education in the city of Mar\u00edlia/SP, in particular, the Creche \u201cIgn\u00e1cio de Loyola Torres\u201d and the Municipal Nursery \u201cM\u00e3e Cristina\u201d? These are questions that guided Josiane de Moura Dias Marquizeli's master's research, the results of which are published in this book. Taking the early childhood education institution where she worked as the object of study, the author developed rigorous documentary and bibliographical research, contributing to the understanding of aspects hitherto little or not explored in the history of early childhood education in Mar\u00edlia. Through knowledge of the past, the research made it possible to understand the present and the debates and actions that took place since at least the 1990s for the recognition of the right of young children to more than being cared for. There have been many advances, but there are still many needs and urgencies for this right to be fully implemented. Civil society plays an important role in this process. And the results of Josiane's research also contribute to this. This is, therefore, an indispensable book for teachers, caregivers, school and public education managers, researchers, undergraduate and graduate students, fathers and mothers. And it can also be considered as another instrument of struggle and an invitation to the necessary debate and urgent collective actions in defense of the education of our children for the construction of a fairer and more inclusive society"
            ],
